==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sufferable
<hw>Suf"fer*a*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>souffrable</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Able to suffer or endure;
patient.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧Ye must be
<xex>sufferable</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That may be suffered, tolerated, or permitted;
allowable; tolerable.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Suf"fer*a*ble*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos> --
<wf>Suf"fer*a*bly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sufferance</ent>⟦br⟧
